      <div type="edition" xml:lang="mi-Latn">
	<p>
	  <lb n="1"/>
	    koṇācikaseṇiya
	  <lb n="2"/>
	    upāsako <persName key="pers:Āḍuthūma">āḍuthūma</persName>
	  <lb n="3"/>
	    sako || <placeName key="pl:Vaḍālikā">vaḍālikāyaṃ</placeName>
	  <lb n="4"/>
	    karajamulanivataṇā<lb n="5" break="no"/>ni 
	    bisa || <placeName key="pl:Kaṭaputaka">kaṭaputake</placeName>
	  <lb n="6"/>
	    vaḍamule nivata<lb n="7" break="no"/>ṇāni <unclear>na</unclear>va
	</p>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
	<p>
	  By <persName key="pers:Āḍuthūma">Āḍuthūma</persName>
	  the Saka, an upāsaka of the guild of Koṇācikas,
	  (a gift of) 20 nivatanas in
	  <placeName key="pl:Vaḍālikā">Vaḍālikā</placeName>
	  near the Karanja tree, and in 
	  <placeName key="pl:Kaṭaputaka">Kaṭaputaka</placeName>,
	  9 nivatanas near the banyan tree.
	</p>
      </div>
